arStrings.szText: Oh, Eru.  He picked a fight he knew he wouldn’t win. Bringing Mephisto into the Vault nearly killed him.
And when it didn’t, he asked us to finish him. To end his pain.
You’re sure this is the right move? Letting him go.
I...know how it feels. To carry the guilt of hurting someone. And I know too well what it’s like to wrestle with the Lord of Hatred. Eru made the only choice he thought he could.
It’s infuriating. It’s crushing. But he’s already done the worst he can do to us.
Let him wrestle with himself, now. It’s what Akarat would want. If we kill him, we rob him of the choice to be better.
It’s time we returned to the Horadric Vault. It might have something, anything that could help us against Mephisto.
